<br>
X wrote<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; It is a heavy booster. It can lift upto 162 tons. Unfortunately, 130 tons of it is brought back to earth every single trip. And that 130 tons belong to the shuttle orbiter.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
My point. The &quot;Shuttle&quot; itself is what they're talking about keeping flying, and calling a heavylifter.<br>
That's the first and most important part to jettison if you want to use NASA hardware to do serious lifting.<br>
Deadweight of the orbiter is far far more than the cargo load...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt;  Drop the orbiter and keep the SSME's, and you have a heavy lift booster for about the same price as a single shuttle launch.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Most importantly, the orbiter is the vastly largest portion of the flight cost of the launch system. Drop the orbiter (the inescapable death-trap money-hog), and the launch cost drops a lot. Maybe more than half -probably more like 20% of what we are used to think of as the cost-per-mass to orbit. (remember this whenever you hear the horror-story figure of $20,000+ per KG in orbit)<br>
 Simply building the ET and SRBs and assembling and fueling it isn't as costly as the army of specialized technical skills needed to refurbish the orbiter between flights. (Remembering also that the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://astronautix.com/lvs/shuttlec.htm">Shuttle-C</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is unmanned, too)<br>
<br>
For my $.02, drop the SSMEs and maybe the SRBs too. Use cheaper Russian engines or maybe use expendable replacements, and the cost drops further. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=854.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=854.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=854.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=854.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.threadControl?topicID=854.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=854.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=854.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://